summary: This man. Mark Sheppard.   That day at the expo I was struggling with my mental health, having a really hard time, crying. I...
caption:
This man. Mark Sheppard.  

That day at the expo I was struggling with my mental health, having a really hard time, crying. I almost skipped the photo op because of how upset I was. Thankfully my dad convinced me to go in. I walk up to him and start bawling, not because of him but because of what happened that day. This man takes my hands, starts calming me down, telling me it’s going to be okay and that I shouldn’t be nervous. Instead of taking the picture while crying he lets me sit down behind the cameras so I could calm down and stop crying, and I was allowed to cut in whenever I was ready. My dad and boyfriend even started crying.

What an amazing man.

title: The Special Child
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2BCFz63

by Katie_The_Hobbit

*Some characters who are dead in the show are alive in this fic*

After more than a decade of hunting alongside his brother, Dean, Sam has finally left the life, leaving his brother to continue the fight while he lives his life in retirement. He met the woman of his dreams, settled down, and had a family. It was, as Dean would call it, the apple pie life he always dreamed of. Sadly, when his wife, Lauren, suddenly passes away, Sam finds himself having to raise their daughter, Emilia, alone, with some help from Dean, who lifts Sam from the dirt and tells him everything is going to be okay.

As Emilia grows older, mysterious things begin to happen, and Sam finds himself being dragged back into the life he so desperately tried to escape. Sam and Dean vow to protect Emilia with their lives, but what will happen when they find out that Emilia isn’t like the other children, that Emilia is special? What will happen when little Emilia finds out she’s different? More importantly, how will Emilia handle meeting those who want to help her, and those who want to kill her?

blog.title: My Words. My Stories.
blog.description: Internet me is sweet as pie, fandom chick who is super fly, Sleepy all day but a writer at night.

body:
Thief- punishment

Pairing: Crowley x Reader

Summary: part two of this, Crowley comes searching for the reader has she’s healing from their last encounter… And the reader is certainly pushing certain buttons

Aruthor’s Note:I’m back!!! Hope you guys like. Let me know! Not as long as I wanted, but ehhh!! Much love! ❤️

Warnings: slightly graphic, nothing to sexual, jerk!crowley

~*~

 Three weeks. Three long, agonizing weeks. You’d been held up in this way less then five star motel, the dust laying on your lungs like a ton of bricks, the scratchy blanket long tossed out for irritating your skin.

   You were bored, and sore. The bruises you had sustained from your encounter with Crowley covered most of your torso in their dark blue/black hue.Luckily you hadn’t seriously been hurt- other then extreme contusions to your ribs that is.

    Your mind wondered back to how mad Crowley was that night. How upset he had seemed when you had mentioned your relationship to the mysterious King of hell. He certainly was very fiercful with his kiss.

    That kiss. What had you been thinking? It was amazing, admitedly, but Crowley was a demon and you were a hunter. You could not let this happen again. Even if that was the best kiss you’d ever recieved, hot and demanding.. 

   “No, Y/n,” you scold yourself out loud softly, “Stop it.”

 “Stop what, poppet?“ Cam the accent deep tone that made you incrediblely weak.

You swung your head around to stare at Crowley, a long irritated breathe escaped your throat as he regarded you, one brow raised with a smirk.

"God damnit, Crowley. Haven’t you demons heard of doors? It’s a very simple concept. You knock on the wood, wait for the reply, and enter. That way you don’t scare the living hell out of whoever’s on the other end!”

“Sweetheart,” he says half jokingly, “what gave you the impression that kings would use doors?”

Your mouth hung open as you starred at him. Was he serious right now? Was he joking? He had to be. He had to be joking. This was just not polite.

Why did it make you wet?

He chuckled. “Now why do you seem confused? Oh, Y/n, first you steal from me, and now English seems to be too hard for you to understand.”

“First off, I didn’t steal from you, you… You pompous jerk!”

“Ah, ah, ah- simple cymatics. You killed one of my best men”

“I didn’t know! And if you’re so angry at me why the hell would you kiss me in the first place!”

His glazed over, becoming the bright demonic color that was slowing turning your limbido into a hot mess.

What the hell was wrong with you?

“I kissed you because I felt like it. I do what I feel like I want to do. I’m a bloody king.”

You rolled your eyes at his comment, deciding pushing his buttons was the only way to get anywhere. Either you would push him far enough he’d leave you to heal, he’d kill you, or he’d kiss you again.

And you couldn’t be sure exactly which one you wanted more.

“You have a complex, Crowley. What is it? So obsessed with everyone obeying you because you want everyone to forget why you sold your soul in the first place?” You held your hand up, index finger and thumb barely spaced apart. “Can’t handle anyone thinking your not up to par anymore can you? Want to be feared instead of laughed at?”

Suddenly you found yourself bound to the bed, hands and legs spread apart, gasping for the air that was knocked out of you.

Crowley came over to the bed silently, the only noise in the room, aside from your breathing, was his shoes as he took long strides to cover the distance. He stood over you with a scowl, and for a second you second guessed your earlier decision to push him.

“You’re walking a thin line, Y/n. I bloody well think you should tread carefully.”

Your blood was boiling now. Demon or not, hurt or not,how dare he just use his powers against you. You were a hunter and you did whatever you damn well pleased.

“Sorry, Crowley,” you began watching his face tyrn into an approving, cocky smirk. “I didn’t realize that a few inches knocked you up so many pegs.”

His face contorted in anger as he snapped his fingers, your clothes disappearing like magic. Air hit your bare skin, as you lay there- bound by him, naked.

He regarded you silently for awhile, appearing to regard the dark purple bruising covering your body.

“Let’s see how many pegs I can ‘knock myself up’ with you, Y/n,"he finally says quietly.

You turn your head to look at him, just as he’s slowly removing his suit jacket. Your mouth runs dry. You watch in almost fascination when he pulls his tie from his neck, watching his muscles bunch and release under the thin silk if his shirt.

"Let me go, Crowley.” You were beginning to have second thoughts. You didn’t much like the idea of being hooked on a demon, or the fact that he’s had centuries to prepare the knowledge of how to be sexually pleasing.

“Tsk, tsk, poppet,” he says, his voice gruff and his eyes glowing, “I told you, King’s don’t do as they’re told.”

“Crowley-”

“Enough, Y/n,” he snaps. “Lay there, quietly. With no complaints, or you will be punished again.”

title: So I just read Good Omens
body:
And the things I learned are:

  • Crowley, An Angel who did not so much Fall as SAUNTERED VAGUELY DOWNWARDS
  • Crowley and Aziraphale are hella gay for each other and I love it
  • threaten the plants so you have the best damn plants in the entire neighborhood
  • when collecting books, it is unwise to actually have a store that says you sell books
  • traffic, bad internet connection, and jammed telephone lines are all good sources of sin
  • when in doubt, consult the local leader of the neighborhood’s trouble kids for advice
  • whales should be saved
  • Crowley and Aziraphale are hella gay for each other and I love it
  • be wary of well-meaning but loony nuns with misleading winks
  • small dogs are the spawns of hell
  • no seriously they’re actually hellhounds
  • the ducks have their own society and preference of bread
  • every spy’s favorite hobby is, of course, feeding the ducks
  • Pestilence has retired from the Horsemen of the Apocalypse due to penicillin
  • Pulsifer is pronounced with a hard ‘s’, and is not, in any way, connected to Lucifer
  • Crowley and Aziraphale are hella gay for each other and I love it

summary: To get myself excited for a three-day weekend of writing fanfic, posting links to all my SPN work: Coda Dean and Sam stand at...
body:
To get myself excited for a three-day weekend of writing fanfic, posting links to all my SPN work:

Coda

Dean and Sam stand at the edge of the lake, just beyond the little cottage where they lost everything and everyone. They mourn together and apart. Mourn a mother, and an angel. And a demon. Missing scene from Ep1 of Season 13. Vignette COMPLETE

https://archiveofourown.org/works/14478945


Cue the Dramatic Entrance

Dean is absolutely certain Crowley is just waiting to make a dramatic entrance, with a perfectly timed “Hello, boys.” Isn’t he? Post-13x13 vignette COMPLETE

https://archiveofourown.org/works/14479020


Find Yourself Here

In an attempt to find himself, Dean considers a series of suburban hobbies without success. COMPLETE.

https://archiveofourown.org/works/14708706


Season 10: Brother’s Keeper

You know what Season 10 needs? A little artistic license. In this summary draft to his publisher and #1 fan, Carver Edlund lays out his plans for the “Supernatural” books after Dean becomes a demon – proving that the SPN writers totally got it wrong. A Season 10 summary rewrite. Demon!Dean, Cured!Crowley, tons of bromance, and unlike the canon – no plot holes! COMPLETE.

https://archiveofourown.org/works/15975470


Pyre - One of the Boys Series

Crowley had long considered throwing off the yoke of kingship and tossing his lot in with the Winchesters. A mangled history of miscalculations on his part and distrust on theirs had delayed what he now wondered might have been inevitable since the night in that church so many years ago. Dean & Crowley friendship vignette. Part of the One of the Boys series. Post-S12 Canon-divergent COMPLETE

https://archiveofourown.org/works/14479104


And lastly: Scene from An Alt!Dimension

The rift closed, and if it hadn’t already, all Hell would’ve break loose. Missing scenes from that alternative dimension, which evolved into the alternative Season 13 finale the fandom and characters deserved. In progress. Working on the final chapter all this long weekend.

https://archiveofourown.org/works/14479146/chapters/33447213
